**Note:** The original error was `com.google.gson.JsonObject is not an interface`.  
The fix is to ensure that `JsonObject` is an interface, or if it is a class, to use a real subclass or mock instead of Proxy.  
If `JsonObject` is a class (not interface), Proxy cannot be used to implement it.  
Assuming `JsonObject` is a class, replace the proxy with a Mockito mock or a subclass.

If `JsonObject` is a class, here is a Mockito-based fix:

```java
package com.google.gson;

import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;
import static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.*;
import static org.mockito.Mockito.*;

class JsonElementTest {

  private static class JsonElementSubclass extends JsonElement {
    @Override
    public JsonElement deepCopy() {
      return this;
    }
  }

  @Test
  void testIsJsonObject_withJsonObjectInstance_returnsTrue() {
    // Use Mockito to create a mock of JsonObject
    JsonObject mockJsonObject = mock(JsonObject.class, invocation -> {
      if ("deepCopy".equals(invocation.getMethod().getName())) {
        return invocation.getMock();
      }
      return invocation.callRealMethod();
    });

    // The mockJsonObject is instance of JsonObject and JsonElement (JsonObject extends JsonElement)
    assertTrue(mockJsonObject.isJsonObject());
  }

  @Test
  void testIsJsonObject_withJsonElementInstance_returnsFalse() {
    JsonElement element = new JsonElementSubclass();
    assertFalse(element.isJsonObject());
  }

}
```

Use this second version if `JsonObject` is a class, not an interface.
